value.0: Doorway from the Electric Castle Hall South, to the Mirror Maze North.
This is a fairly strong and heavy looking wooden door.
Fashioned from rough iron, these bars extend into a narrow slot in the floor.
Detailed carvings cover the surface of this finely-crafted door. The handiwork is of high quality and no doubt came at quite an expense.

Low and flat, this chest seems to have been designed for the storage and filing of a merchant's accounts.
This key bears the moniker "Electric Castle" engraved along it's shaft.

Warning!

You have entered the Electric Castle. Three passages lead further in. The wrong path will surely lead to your doom. 

Each must follow their own path. Follow the path that best represents your soul. 

Choose wisely, and you will be rewarded. Choose wrong, and you will be rejected. 

Do not travel further in until you are ready. There will be no returning here.
With the face turned down, it's hard to determine if the victim was male or female.

The old shelves, and musty tomes, are covered with a thick layer of dust and cobwebs. Many of the books look as though they might crumble if touched. Only one appears to be in half-decent condition. 

It appears nobody has read anything off these shelves in quite some time.

This seems to be the journal of somebody who was staying in this locked room. There is no sign of whoever it was, but maybe the journal can give you some insight. 

Most of the pages are faded or crumbled, but you are able to makeout a few entries:

Day 3 - I managed to surv... .he mon..ers in t.e Mirr.r .aze, and a.ter much trial an. e.ror I fo..d the path through. The famed Electric Castle is no. like i. was des.r.bed. Monst..s are every..ere, and only my sk..lls at hidin. have ke.t me safe. Th.s lo..ed room seem. to be t.e only re.uge in this cursed place.

I've explor.. th.s entire le..l of the castle, the Hall. All exc..t the three pathways. I don't dare enter them until I am s..e of the answ.. to the signs warning. 

Day 17 - Running out of su..lies, but I ..ink I .av. solv.d the thr.e paths. It says to pick the on. th.t be.. r...esent. yo.r soul, and the onl. clu. se.ms to be the coloured lig.ts. I think Red is sa..e for evil-soul.d indi...als, blue f.. those wit. no predilections for g..d or evil, a.d wh.te ..r g.od-hear.ed folk. But, how do.s one know wh..ch th.y are? 

Day 18 - To..ay mark.d the last of my fo.d. I will choose my path, sin.e the ..easure is the wh.le re..one I came to t.is insane place. I wond.r wh.t has beco.e of Ay.. --- wait....I forgot to lock th. doo....--_______

At that point, there is a scribble of ink, and the rest of the page is torn out. There are no further entries in the journal.
A pile of books, carelessly discarded.
The books lay piled atop each other with little in the way of rhyme or reason, as if someone was interrupted while in the process of returning them to their place.
